      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De dementia</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in
              <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e112">Minor est virtus certaminis, foris quempiam
              videre mala quae superet, et intus quod toleret non habere. Perfectae autem
              mansuetudinis et clementiae laus est, adversa perpeti, et exterius fortiter, et
              interius clementer.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e119">Augustinus, in
              <title>Sermone Domini in monte</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e127">Mitis est, qui cedit improbitatibus, et non
              resistit in malo, sed vincit in bono malum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e134">Augustinus, in
              <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e142">Malis parce, vir mitis et bone; et quanto melior
              es, tanto mitior esto; et quanto sis celsior potestate, tanto humilior fias
              pietate.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e149">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>super Matthaeum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e157">Mansuetus neque irritat malum, neque irritatur a
              malo, neque adversus eum praevalet causa peccati, neque adversus alterum aliquando ex
              illo nascitur causa peccandi: sed magis contentus est injuriam pati, quam
              facere.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e165">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>super Matthaeum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e173">Ille est vere mansuetus, qui cum nocitus fuerit
              ab alio, nec cogitat facere malum, nec facit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e180">Joannes
            Chrysostomus, <title>super Joannem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e188">Si cogitaverimus quoniam non ei qui
              contristavit, sed nobisipsis largimur, cito dimittemus venenum irae et
              vindictae.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e195">Ambrosius,
              <title>in Lucam</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e203">Non habet ultionis studium perfecta virtus; nec
              ulla est iracundia, ubi plenitudo est charitatis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e210">Isidorus, in
              <title>Synonymis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e218">Aufer a corde fraternam offensionem; alienae
              nequitiae non serves dolorem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e225">Isidorus, in
              <title>Synonymis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e233">Supplici oranti veniam deprecare; petenti quoque
              tibi veniam, libenter indulge.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e245" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e240">Beda, in glossa,
            Luc. IX</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e245">Non semper in eos, qui peccant, est vindicandum;
              quia nunquam amplius prodest clementia tibi ad patientiam, lapso ad
              correctionem.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e251">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e261" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e253">Seneca, <title>de
              Clementia</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e261">Verecundiam peccandi facit ipsa clementia
              regentis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e266">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e276" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e268">Seneca, <title>de
              Clementia</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e276">Magni animi proprium est, placidum esse
              tranquillumque, et injurias atque offensiones spernere.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e281">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e291" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e283">Seneca, <title>de
              Clementia</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e291">Clementem vocabo non in alieno dolore facilem,
              sed eum qui, cum suis stimulis exagitetur, non prosilit; qui intelligit magni animi
              esse injurias in summa potentia pati, nec quidquam esse gloriosius principe impune
              laeso.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-d1e296">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e306" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Rd1e298">Seneca, <title>de
              Clementia</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e24426-Qd1e306">Nullum clementia ex omnibus magis quam principem
              decet. Nam pestifera vis est, valere ad nocendum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
